Summary: Biochemical reaction from vitamin K1 epoxide to Vitamin K. This interaction can be catalyzed by EPHX1 or VKORC1.
Biochemical reaction from Vitamin K to hydroxy-vitamin K. This interaction is catalyzed by CYP4F2.
Biochemical reaction from Vitamin K to vitamin K dihydroquinone. This interaction can be catalyzed by NQO1, VKORC1 or AIFM2.
Biochemical reaction from vitamin K dihydroquinone to vitamin K1 epoxide. This interaction is catalyzed by GGCX.
